Commentary: tossed up outside off and what a start for Taylor, his feet moving nicely into the ball, opens the face and drives it through the covers
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Taylor, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower and and tossed up again, makes him reach, Taylor pushes and nearly lobs it to cover this time
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Taylor, no run

Commentary: shorter and quicker around off, pushed down the ground to long-off for one
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: full and angled in, Masakadza looks to blast this down the ground but doesn't time it
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: slower and full around middle, Masakadza pushes at it but eludes Shakib to his right for one to mid-on
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, 1 run

Commentary: slower and shorter outside off, Taylor turns it around towards midwicket off the backfoot for one
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: would you believe it, wicket first ball for Taijul and the crowd erupts! It was tossed up around middle and off, Taylor went for the slog sweep first up but seemed to have misjudged the length which was slightly shorter than he would have liked, the extra bounce induced the top edge, taken easily at short third man. Poor shot, it has to be said
Dismissal_text: BRM Taylor c Mahmudullah b Taijul Islam 6 (5b 1x4 0x6) SR: 120.00

Commentary: length around off, pushed down the ground for one
length around the pads, spins down the leg side
length and angled across, pushed into the covers
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Ervine, no run

Commentary: length around middle and leg, the ball grips off the surface and cramps him for room
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Ervine, no run

Commentary: big appeal but turned down! It was full around middle, seemed to pitch on and straighten as he played around his front pad and missed
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Ervine, no run

Commentary: similar delivery, ,maybe slightly shorter around middle, plays around the front pad again but gets an inside edge on to pad
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Ervine, no run

Commentary: full around middle, pushed back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: shorter outside off, pushed into the covers
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: quicker and flatter, angled in, he makes room to open up the off side but can't beat cover
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: fuller and angled in and Masakadza breaks the shackles with a powerful sweep, flat and hard, behind square for four
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: full and angled in, he skips down the wicket, gets to the pitch and hammers it past mid-on for another four
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: shorter and wider outside off, punches it hard off the backfoot but can't pierce the cover field on this occasion
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: length and around the pads, spins down the leg side
landing outside off, fetched uppishly into the leg side, but can't beat midwicket
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Ervine, no run

Commentary: drifting wide of the off stump, he throws his hands into a drive and slices to short third man for a single
beaten by turn and bounce! The ball dips on him and then rips away from a poke outside off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: attempted reverse sweep now, but it zips past him into the keeper's gloves
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: flatter, aimed at the off stump, and it's chopped hard, but straight to cover
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: this time he nails it! Another reverse sweep, but this time he gets an excellent connection to slap it with the spin, down to third man
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: and he starts with a nippy yorker, the ball dipping and swinging in to Ervine's boot. There's a speculative appeal, but that was headed down leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Ervine, 1 leg bye

Commentary: more shape away from the right hander, tapped to cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: another yorker, but it's not quite on the mark, dug out to mid on and they pinch a quick single
curving in towards Ervine's pads, and he's nudged just wide of midwicket for another single
picked up over fine leg! Trademark shot from Masakadza, putting his left leg down the track and bending down low to scoop a length ball up over the fielder at fine leg, using the pace
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: this one's aimed directly at the off stump, Masakadza pushing to cover and sending Ervine back with a loud 'no!'
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: powerfully swept! Ervine got himself into a good position, sweeping over the top of it and cracking the ball right into the gap at deep square leg
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Ervine, FOUR runs

Commentary: he's down the track this time, skipping into position and chipping the ball out to deep midwicket
a touch flatter this time, and it's flicked along the ground to that man at deep midwicket
HUGE! Masakadza gets down on one knee, opens those broad shoulders and smears a slog sweep into stands beyond midwicket
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Masakadza, SIX runs

Commentary: too short, too wide! Taijul over-corrects, spearing the ball in short outside off. Masakadza leans back and spanks a cut behind square
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: that's better, held back a touch and Masakadza has to wait on it before punching out to deep cover
he starts straight, on a length, and is worked just wide of midwicket for a single

just wide of a diving fielder! Mustafizur drifts into Ervine's pads and is clipped into the leg side, but uppishly and only just wide of a diving Mahmudullah inside the circle. They're back for two, bringing up the fifty
beaten outside off, the ball angling in and then nipping away from Ervine, who had set himself to flick to leg but missed completely
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Ervine, no run

Commentary: short, pulled, and caught! Ervine didn't look too rushed, but simply didn't time it as he'd have liked. Mosaddek was perfectly positioned at deep midwicket, and juggles the take, but holds on
Dismissal_text: CR Ervine c Mosaddek Hossain b Mustafizur Rahman 11 (14b 1x4 0x6) SR: 78.57

Commentary: pitched right up to him, and snaking in through the air. Masakadza digs it out back at the bowler
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: full once more, but slower this time. Masakadza reads it, and finds space just wide of mid off for a single
he makes room early, backing away to leg, but the bowler follows him and there's not much room to work with. Tapped down the ground, just the one
big swing! Williams is a little fortunate as this curves sharply in to him, taking the inside half of the bat and rolling to leg to get him off the mark
down the track comes Masakadza, slugging a single down to long on
a touch of width outside off now, and he's crunched neatly out to deep cover

slapped in the air, snaffled at mid off! Again Masakadza made room, but Saifuddin followed him, cramping his attempted smear down the ground. He couldn't get under it, and Sabbir tumbles forward at mid off to hold a very sharp catch
Dismissal_text: H Masakadza c Sabbir Rahman b Mohammad Saifuddin 34 (26b 5x4 1x6) SR: 130.76

Commentary: this one hits the seam and comes back in to him, Maruma working him softly into the leg side
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Maruma, no run

Commentary: and he strikes first ball! Williams is caught in two minds, aiming down the ground but checking his shot. The end result is the simplest of return catches back to Mosaddek
Dismissal_text: SC Williams c & b Mosaddek Hossain 2 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

Commentary: quicker, flatter and rushing on with the arm. Burl is forward to keep it out
Commentary_short: Mosaddek Hossain to Burl, no run

Commentary: he makes room now, cutting straight to point
Commentary_short: Mosaddek Hossain to Burl, no run

Commentary: Burl reaches out at a wide one, driving to long off to get off the mark
reverse paddle sweep from Maruma, who has to jam the bat down to get something on a very full one
worked off the toes, into the leg side, and a single keeps him on strike
classy drive! Mustafizur offers up a full, wide half volley. Burl leans forward and opens the face of the bat to drive behind point with poise and timing
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Burl, FOUR runs

Commentary: just short of mid off! Burl is suckered into another drive, but this one's slower and Mustafizur has rolled his fingers over it. He's way too early into the shot, but the timing is so bad that it doesn't quite reach the mid off fielder diving forward
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Burl, no run

Commentary: needless run out! Burl fends a quicker one into the leg side, and Maruma sets off. Burl initially takes a step down the wicket, but then stops and sends him back. But he's too late. Maruma turns on his heels and dives for his crease, but a sharp throw from Shakib catches him short, Mustafizur getting himself into position and whipping the bails off
Dismissal_text: T Maruma run out (Shakib Al Hasan/Mustafizur Rahman) 1 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: flung down wide outside off
full and swinging in from outside off, Burl's drive being stopped at cover
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Burl, no run

Commentary: another slower one. Burl aims for mid off, but the cut on the ball means it goes to mid on instead
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Burl, no run

Commentary: aimed very full, at his toes, and Burl digs it out to midwicket
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Burl, no run

Commentary: around the wicket comes Mosaddek, Tino flicking off the pads but finding short fine leg
Commentary_short: Mosaddek Hossain to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: again he aims a flick, this time the ball touches the pad and they pinch a quick single
Commentary_short: Mosaddek Hossain to Mutombodzi, 1 leg bye

Commentary: Burl waits deep in the crease and works a length ball into the gap on the leg side, quick single
flatter, aimed at his pads from around the stumps. Nudged at midwicket
Commentary_short: Mosaddek Hossain to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: punched a little more firmly this time, down to long on
floated up a little slower, glanced off the pads just wide of midwicket
reverse swept, straight at the short third man fielder, but they take him on with a quick single, and win
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, 1 run

Commentary: another tip-and-run single, Mutombodzi putting bat to ball towards cover and setting off
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: Burl backs away acres towards the leg side, but Shakib follows him with a dart that zips under his bat, and past the leg stump
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, no run

Commentary: this time he stays put, tapping back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, no run

Commentary: another reverse sweep, this one finds the gap and a single
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, 1 run

Commentary: he skips down the track to get close to it, working it out to deep midwicket to keep the strike
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: again he uses his feet, getting to the pitch and crunching a drive down to long on
drifting in towards his pads, and Burl finds a gap in front of square
beaten outside off! It was a quicker one, rushing straight on with the arm to beat him
Commentary_short: Mosaddek Hossain to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: quick again, and he's down the wicket to meet it but can't quite get to the pitch. Mosaddek charges down the pitch and hurls a shy to send him scurrying back to the crease
Commentary_short: Mosaddek Hossain to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: slog swept into the leg side, and they hurry back for a second. He didn't get all of it, and the ball flew just past a diving Shakib at midwicket. That wasn't far away
shorter this time, but he can't make the most of the long hop, pulling hard but straight to Shakib at midwicket
Commentary_short: Mosaddek Hossain to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: Burl jumps down the track, slashing a length ball out to the sweeper
a yorker goes wrong, coming out as a low full toss, and it's flapped firmly into the leg side
huge heave from Tino, but he can't get anything on it
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: slower bouncer, and he finds himself in an awkward position as he mis-reads it, the ball looping past him
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: another slower ball, and now he's down on bended knee to crack it out to deep midwicket
Saifuddin ends an excellent over with a very full one, outside off, that Mutombodzi digs out but can't put away
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: yorker, swinging in from outside off, and it's jammed out to cover
good-looking flick from Tino, but the placement's not quite there to find the boundary

crunched over wide long on! Mustafizur has got the better of Burl with a couple of slower ones, but this one was read well and timed even better. A little step back and across made room, and he spanked the leather off it
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Burl, SIX runs

Commentary: innovation now, Burl walking across to the off side and keeping his eye on the ball to scoop a full one up and over the fine leg fielder
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Burl, FOUR runs

Commentary: rattled! Burl stands still at the crease but Mustafizur sprays this well wide outside off
he follows him with a short ball, Burl muscling a pull out to deep midwicket
another short one, a slower bouncer, and Tino almost swings himself off his feet trying to deposit this over the leg side. But the ball loops past him, and he's only hit fresh air
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: and there's Burl! He takes a couple of steps to the off side, creating the line he wants, and swings a MASSIVE six over deep backward square with a big slog sweep
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, SIX runs

Commentary: crunched down the ground now! Shakib darts this in quicker, but it's too short and Burl slams a pull straight back past him, beating the diving long on
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, FOUR runs

Commentary: and now the reverse sweep, Burl getting himself quickly into position before the ball arrives and placing the shot perfectly
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, FOUR runs

Commentary: carnage! The ball is floated up harmlessly on his toes, and Burl opens his shoulders to swipe it over square leg. The fielder out there was briefly interested in it, but it flew over his head
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, SIX runs

Commentary: Burl is unstoppable, bending down low and spanking the ball cleanly into the leg side, placing it right between the two fielders out there
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, FOUR runs

Commentary: fifty up, and what a way to get there! Burl stands still at the crease, sizes up a full one, and swings it cleanly down the ground. His maiden T20I fifty, and a vital one for Zimbabwe
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Burl, SIX runs

Commentary: pinpoint yorker, just outside off, and it's dug out into the off side. Burl spots the chance for a quick single, and calls him through
slower ball, on a length, and it's fetched out to deep midwicket
another nippy yorker, and Tino does well to put bat to ball, getting it into the leg side to turn the strike back over
a slower ball bouncer, and he spots it early but can't quite place the pull
Tino joins the party! Length from the bowler, and he was set in the crease and waiting for it. He gets an excellent connection, and the ball flies way over the fielder's head at deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Mutombodzi, SIX runs

Commentary: another yorker, and he can't get under it, picking up a single to long off
full, wide yorker to start, and he digs it out to the cover sweeper, putting Burl back on strike
Burl in a tangle! He walks right across to off and looks to set himself for a paddle-scoop, but Mustafizur follows him and Burl almost falls over his own feet
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Burl, no run

Commentary: slashing square drive now, but he can't beat the deep point fielder
full toss, outside off, and Tino flings his hands out into a drive. A thick edge flies past the keeper, and it has the beating of third man too
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Mutombodzi, FOUR runs

Commentary: ouch! Mutombodzi swings hard and inside edges the ball straight onto his own knee. Burl wants a single, but Tino is on the ground and can't go anywhere. The ball struck him just above the knee roll
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: big drive, inside out over wide mid off. Did Soumya lose it in the lights? He wasn't too quick off the mark, and the ball comes safely to ground. They hurry back for the second
length around off, hint of turn away, he watches it closely under his eyes and defends
Commentary_short: Williams to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: short and around off, spinning away, Liton has plenty of time to wait for it to come and turn it around towards midwicket with his wrists
full around middle, Soumya plants his frontfoot across and has to play around it, manages to push it to midwicket and they scamper a single that ideally shouldn't have been there
short and angled in, Liton makes room to open up the off side, cuts it straight to point
Commentary_short: Williams to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: Liton seems to have a measure of the bowling by now and he's deposited that over deep backward square leg! It was angled in on a length, he shuffled across to get inside the line and just helped it along with the angle, the final flourish giving him the power to clear the ropes
Commentary_short: Williams to Liton Das, SIX runs

Commentary: slower and fuller around off, waits for it and defends off the backfoot
Commentary_short: Williams to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: full on the pads, tickled towards short fine leg off an inside edge that took a bit of pad with it
length and angled in, nearly chipped to short fine-leg as Liton picked it up off his hip, of course, it would have been four either side, so decide who's unlucky there
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: overpitched around off and Liton goes through the line and over the bowler's head for a glorious boundary down the ground
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, FOUR runs

Commentary: shortens his length, around off again, Liton swats this over the cover field but the timing's not great for more than two
length and angled in, slower ball, tucked away towards midwicket and it's going to be free hit for a front foot no-ball. Sloppy from Zimbabwe
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, (no ball) 1 run

Commentary: excellent come back! Held his nerve, banged it half way down but slowed it up appreciably, completely deceived Soumya who was through his flat batted stroke way too early
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: bouncer, around middle and Soumya's beaten for pace this time as he misses the pull. Good comeback from Jarvis
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: wide on the crease, length around off, squared him up almost as it was threatening to come in with the angle but straightened, played nice and late in the end, taps it to the off side for one
length around middle, bit of nibble back in cramping Soumya for room, but he taps it near his feet and they take off for one
another no ball, another free hit, it was length around off, steered to point, who palmed it over his head to allow one and what's more, they steam another on the overthrow
Commentary_short: Chatara to Liton Das, (no ball) 2 runs

Commentary: slower one, short outside off, Liton waits for it and slaps it over backward point and to third-man's right on a couple of bounces for another couple
length outside off, Liton shuffles way outside off, looking to scoop this perhaps, but it's too wide for him to fetch, gets a legbye as the ball deflects fine off the shoulder
Commentary_short: Chatara to Liton Das, 1 leg bye

Commentary: length around off, airy-fairy drive from Soumya as he looks to go through the covers, and nearly chips one to mid-off

cleans him up with an inch-perfect yorker! Liton backed away too far and too soon, so far they were feeding him outside off, but this was straight, full and right up in the blockhole. Zimbabwe have an opening after a pretty shoddy start

slower ball full around off and the impetuousness of the Bangladesh batsmen is showing! Soumya Sarkar wanted to loft this over the infield, got it off the toe end and just scooped a simple catch to mid-off to really bring Zimbabwe into the game here
Dismissal_text: Soumya Sarkar c Madziva b Jarvis 4 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

Commentary: banged in hard into the surface and at Shakib's body, he fends it off awkwardly towards short fine leg but manages to keep it down
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Shakib Al Hasan, no run

Commentary: nearly chipped to mid-off! Slower ball outside off, holds in the surface, Shakib pushes with his hands way in front and nearly spoons a catch to mid-off, running to his right
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run

Commentary: short one at the body does trickl! Mushfiqur was looking to help this along somewhere towards fine-leg but seemed to take his eyes off it as it hurried onto him and took the shoulder of the blade for a simple catch to Taylor behind the wickets
Dismissal_text: Mushfiqur Rahim c †Taylor b Jarvis 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: another one short around off, lets it through
slower one, off cutter around off, grips off the surface and comes sharply back into Mahmudullah, who does well to tap it near his feet and take off for a quick single
wide on the crease and full outside off with a hint of away movement, left alone
full around off, Mahmudullah was shuffling across to cover the swing, got into a bit of an awkward tangle but manages to push it to the leg side for one

and Shakib goes to an atrocious stroke! It was a length ball, angled across, Shakib was rooted to the crease and chased it with just his hands, only managing a healthy nick to slip to leave his team precariously placed
Commentary_short: Chatara to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Shakib Al Hasan c Masakadza b Chatara 1 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33

Commentary: full around off, pushed to mid-on and they come through for a quick single
length outside off, left alone
length outside off, and Bangladesh continue to play their shots, Sabbir this time, fetches it and flat bats it past mid-on, like a tennis shot for four
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Sabbir Rahman, FOUR runs

Commentary: short one at the body, pulls this time, but with control and along the ground to deep backward square leg

snorter but somehow none of three people converging manage to get to it! That was another short one at the body, Mahmudullah tried to awkwardly turn it around to the leg side, much like Mushfiqur, it took the shoulder off the bat as he kind of took his eyes of at the last instant, but survives despite the hang time it had with the keeper, slip and bowler all interested at one point, but neither getting to it
full outside off, drives but straight to cover
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: another short one, he takes it on but this one held in the surface a little, killing the timing, as he pulled towards square leg
full and angled in, goes for the sweep and misses and so does the keeper, as it deflects fine off Taylor's thigh
flatter one around middle,goes back and pushes it towards long-on
full and drifting in a little, nudged towards deep square leg for one
full outside off, in the slot and driven nicely through the covers, but not placed well enough to beat long-off, who does well to cut it off and keep them to two
flatter one on middle, goes back and pulls it along the ground to deep midwicket
another short one, another pulled hard and flat but straight to deep square leg on the bounce

another short one, this one holds in the surface as he's through the pull shot early, the top edge hangs in their air towards deep square leg, who makes a valiant effort with a full length dive after making plenty of ground, but the ball, as it often does, pops out as the elbows hit the turf
length outside off, too much width and he carves it away through point, and also beats third-man to his right
full on middle, pushed to midwicket
full and angled in, slides down the leg side
length around off, nips back sharply off the seam as he looks to defend with half a bat
length around off, gets it to jag back in again, Mahmudullah waits for it to do its thing, opens the face and runs it down to third man for one
slower short one outside off, Sabbir attempts about three shots but it still never comes on and eventually goes past his slashing blade
Commentary_short: Madziva to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: plays back to a flatter one and given by the umpire, Burl's having a ball! Looks very very leg side, it was a length ball, angled in, he tried to work it to the leg side off the backfoot and missed as it skid on, he reviews but ball tracking reveals it would have just kissed leg stump. Pretty unlucky, you'd have to say, didn't look out to begin with. But since the decision was out, the benefit of doubt goes to the umpire
full around off, pushed down the ground for one

Commentary_short: Burl to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: full on middle, almost a yorker, squeezed away to short third man, there's a bit of confusion with the running but the non striker makes it back in time
Commentary_short: Burl to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: flatter one around off, cut away to deep cover-point
full around off, pushed to extra cover
Commentary_short: Burl to Mosaddek Hossain, no run

Commentary: length around off, backs away and swats it to long-on for one
length outside off, steered to point

Burl's back in play and takes a blinder! Just can't keep him out of the game! It was full outside off, he shuffled and slog swept it high into the night sky to the left of deep square leg, from where Burl had to make considerable ground before diving full length and grabbing it inches from the ground
Dismissal_text: Sabbir Rahman c Burl b Madziva 15 (15b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: full on middle, pushed to long-on
length around off and Bangladesh are going to go down swinging, if at all, this was in the slot, and went through the line and over the bowler's head
Commentary_short: Madziva to Afif Hossain, FOUR runs

Commentary: length outside off, left alone
Commentary_short: Madziva to Afif Hossain, no run

Commentary: fired in full around off, comes down and swings, gets a thick outside edge to short third man
Commentary_short: Williams to Mosaddek Hossain, no run

Commentary: full and fired in on middle, makes a little room and swats it to long-off for one
full outside off, in the slot with plenty of width and he opens the face to find the gap and powers it through the covers
Commentary_short: Williams to Afif Hossain, FOUR runs

Commentary: full and angled across, he skips down the wicket, gets to the pitch and whips it through midwicket, giving the diving long-on no chance
Commentary_short: Williams to Afif Hossain, FOUR runs

Commentary: even quicker and flatter around middle, defended
Commentary_short: Williams to Afif Hossain, no run

Commentary: fired in around middle and off but it's full toss, or made into one as he advances again and has an almighty swing to the leg side, manages to clear wide long-on with easy to breathe some life into this chase
Commentary_short: Williams to Afif Hossain, SIX runs

Commentary: down the wicket and lofted over long-on! It was full and angled in, he got to the pitch and launched it high and handsome over long-on
Commentary_short: Burl to Mosaddek Hossain, SIX runs

Commentary: tossed up again and he comes down, makes a little room and goes inside out this time, even better shot as he manages clear the extra cover fence and the crowd's found its voice again
Commentary_short: Burl to Mosaddek Hossain, SIX runs

Commentary: length and angled across, he shuffles and nudges it towards square leg
full outside off, skips down and blasts this past the bowler's right but can't beat long-on
full around off, he lunges forward and defends to the off side and they come through for a quick single. Brain and brawn in equal measure in this partnership
and now some luck, as he miscues that straight up over the keeper on the pull as the short ball hurries onto him, what's more, it's four
Commentary_short: Chatara to Afif Hossain, FOUR runs

Commentary: length around off, steered to third-man for one

Commentary: length and fired in on middle, he makes room to open up the off side, it skids on, bounces a little extra and seems to take the outside edge but the umpires says not out. Zimbabwe review immediately and it appears that there was nothing on ultra edge as the ball passed the bat, so good decision

Commentary: full and angled in, skips down and hammers it straight but it ricochets off the non striker's bat towards the mid-off region for one
length and angled across, he shuffles and pushes it to long-on
short one on middle, rocks back and pulls along the ground to deep midwicket's left, where the fielder puts in an excellent dive to keep them to two
fired in towards leg, he attempts a reverse sweep and misses but the keeper's fumbles to allow one, it was a tough take, however

what's happened there? It was full outside off, he came down the track and almost perfectly succeeded in bisecting long-off and long-on, before the latter put in a dive to his right, only to push the ball away from the converging fielder and into the boundary

short one, hurries on to him as he attempts to help it along but misses

Commentary: picks the other side this time and with equally good results, it was full and angled across, he shuffled, went down on one knee again and scooped it over the keeper's left shoulder

full toss on middle and he smokes this past the bowler, bisects long-on and long-off with precision and has the power to take it past the boundary

Commentary: length around off, slapped to long-off, they decide to come for the second and Mosaddek was gone had the bowler collected the throw, but he drops the ball and knocks the bails off with his hands. Zimbabwe seems pretty deflated now

another run out chance but can't hit direct and that's young Afif's maiden fifty in only his second game! Full toss on off, steered to point, they take off and Mosaddek had had given up had the fielder hit. The moment, however, belongs to 19-year old Afif, who has swung the game Bangladesh's way from a hopeless situation
short one, pulls along the ground with control and with the fielder in the deep hanging on his heels, they come through for the second
full toss outside off, drilled to extra cover but the captain, Hamilton Masakadza takes it calmly to his right to buy Zimbabwe time. End of a fine T20 innings from the youngster
Dismissal_text: Afif Hossain c Masakadza b Madziva 52 (26b 8x4 1x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: full toss on middle and off, he lofts it over the mid-off, it wasn't off the middle but he cleared the man comfortably enough for two
length and angled across and he swipes this across the line to finish a game that looked well out of their reach not too long ago
